The biggest sensation of the festive season has to have been Senator Irungu Kang’ata’s letter discussing the bleakish prospects of the Building Bridges Initiative, BBI, in the Mt Kenya region.
Several reasons were cited for the weakly flickering performance of an initiative backed by the full strength of state power. Two stood out as particularly concerning. First, the legislator took issue with the use of the provincial administration (and other forms of hard tactics) in BBI mobilisation, which is “an example of government using its hard power to force its citizens to endorse BBI”.



