Regardless of what the law says, they are wholly unrestrained in their repressive crusade.
There is an urgent need to investigate the working environment which seems to create incentives for civil servants to become sordid political actors. Perhaps the feedback system is only an echo chamber where perversity is reinforced and privileged.
In any event, as Kang’ata pointed out, civil servants should not be propagating partisan political agendas. They are hopeless at it, and may be counted on to do irreparable damage, not only to the credibility and effectiveness of the service, but to their ill-fated political projects as well.



